<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE> gauss  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE> May, 2006 </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="gauss"> filters the field through a Gaussian intensity filter.  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[field_out]=gauss(field_in,R[,x_shift[,y_shift[,A]]])  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>field_in  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>:input field. it must be diffractive wavefront. </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>R  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: the radius of the aperture in meters. </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>x_shift  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: the shifts of the X direction in meters. ( default is 0.) </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>y_shift  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>:  the shifts of the Y direction in meters. ( default is 0.) </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>A </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: the coefficient of intensity. ( default is 1.) </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>  
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>field_out  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: the output field or diffractive wavefront. </SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    The transmitted intensity is given by A*exp(-(x*x+y*y)/(R*R)):
    where R is the radius of the Gaussian aperture and A is the maximum
    transmission. This filter can be used to model gauss beams: 
    begin followed by gauss produces a finite grid approximation 
    of a gauss beam. 
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
	F1=begin(0.01,1e-6);
	F2=gauss(F1,0.004);
	field_plot(F2);
	dwf_fits(F2,"F2");	
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
